# BLoC

- Use `flutter_bloc`; one bloc per screen or cohesive flow.
- States and events extend `Equatable` for value equality.
- Name files: `<feature>_bloc.dart`, `<feature>_event.dart`, `<feature>_state.dart`.
- Blocs call **use cases** only — never datasources or APIs directly.
- Emit loading → success/error states; avoid redundant emissions.
- Register blocs in feature `bindings/` via `get_it` / `injectable`.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — bloc delegates to use case
on<LoadDashboard>(_onLoadDashboard);

Future<void> _onLoadDashboard(LoadDashboard event, Emitter emit) async {
  emit(const DashboardLoading());
  final result = await _getDashboardData(const NoParams());
  result.fold(
    (failure) => emit(DashboardError(failure.message)),
    (data) => emit(DashboardLoaded(data)),
  );
}
```
